channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Russian Gains in Ukraine War Worry U.S. Officials
item.description: Multiple factors are helping Russia’s military advance, including a delay in American weaponry and Moscow’s technological innovations on the battlefield.

item.title: Ukraine Says It Is Engaged in Fierce Fighting With Russia in Northeast
item.description: While Ukrainian officials and analysts said that a Russian advance across the border appeared to be slowing, President Volodymyr Zelensky canceled his participation in international events.

item.title: College grads need $99,081 salary offer to change jobs, New York Fed survey says
item.description: The silver lining for employers: Six-figure salary jobs are hard to come by.

item.title: What Alice Munro Would Never Do
item.description: We are very different writers, but I have kept Alice Munro in mind, daily and for decades, as an example to follow.

item.title: U.S. Advances Arms Sale to Israel as It Delays Delivering Other Weapons
Trade and investment data in the last two years dispel the deglobalization and decoupling myths as U.S.-China competition ignites reglobalization
item.description: It's not decoupling or deglobalization, it's reglobalization.

item.title: Putin Is Selling Victory, and Many Russians Are Buying It
item.description: Vladimir Putin’s message to his country appears to be taking hold: that Russia is fighting against the whole Western world — and winning.

item.title: Africa’s car-making juggernaut prepares to capitalize on global race to produce affordable EVs at scale
item.description: As Europe works to phase out combustion engines over the next decade, automakers like Renault are preparing to adapt in Morocco.

item.title: Hundreds of Officers Pursue Manhunt After Deadly Ambush in France
item.description: As a search for the assailants and the prisoner they freed stretched into a second day, the authorities said the assault was surprising given that the inmate was not high-profile.

item.title: U.K. tax authority HMRC kept Brits on hold for nearly 800 years last fiscal year—and it’s getting worse
item.description: Advisors from HMRC answered just 20.5 million out of 38 million calls between 2022 and 2023.

item.title: Sage, a Miniature Poodle, Wins Best in Show at Westminster
item.description: A miniature poodle outlasted a favored giant schnauzer and a crowd-pleasing German shepherd to win the top prize at Westminster.

item.title: UN Begins Citing a Lower Death Toll For Women and Children in Gaza
item.description: The U.N. has begun citing a much lower death toll for women and children in Israel’s military offensive, acknowledging that it has incomplete information about many of those killed.

item.title: British billionaire Joe Lewis' pilot pleads guilty to tax evasion
item.description: In 2019 Lewis loaned his pilots $500,000 each to buy Mirati shares ahead of the trial results being made public.
